history.content:
I'm not sure Math 110 would help directly; it's a very different style of linear algebra. In 110, you're more concerned with theoretical linear algebra and in EE 127, you're very much concerned with practical linear algebra. For example, I don't think you do the SVD in 110 anymore (when I took it, you did it for one day) but that's pretty much all you do in 127 (hyperbole, obviously).

Edit (Dibya): The additional familiarity with Linear Algebra that you gain in 110, as well as working with transformations and projections, do help you gain visual intuition for the concepts that surround the LA in 127. Although not directly relevant, if you feel unfamiliar / uncomfortable with handling and dealing with matrix expressions, then 110 may help develop mathematical maturity before entering 127.

Edit 2 (Andy): Agree with Dibya.
